            <div class="modal-body">Climate:<br> Being a tropical crop, banana requires warm, humid and rainy climate.
                The optimum temperature range is 10 to
                400C and the relative humidity is 90% or above. It is highly susceptible to frost and cannot tolerate
                arid conditions.
                Strong desiccating winds cause considerable reduction in the growth of the plant and yield and quality
                of fruits. <br><br>Soil:<br> Banana is a heavy feeder crop/. Therefore, fertility of soil is very
                important. Rich, well drained, fertile, free
                working, soils with plenty of organic matter are best suited for cultivation. The optimum range of pH of
                soil should be
                6 to 8.</div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <button class="link modal-close">CLOSE</button>
            </div>
