                </button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
            
            Gaint kew or kew:-<br> It is one of the most important cultivars of Pineapple . It is ideal for canning industry. Flesh of
            the fruit is yellow, fibreless and juicy. The fruit is cylindrical in shape with average weight 1.9 kg . It is a late
            maturing variety.<br><br>
            
            Queen :- <br>It is the second important cultivar which is grown in our country. It is an early maturing variety, used as
            table variety. It is mostly grown in Bengal region. The fruits are small cylindrical, with average weight 1.2 kg. Fruit
            colour is golden yellow while the flesh is deep golden yellow.<br><br>
            
            Mauritius :- <br>It is a mid season variety. Fruits of this variety are medium sized with yellow and red skin.
            
            </div>
